{% block title %}Recommend{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="container">
    <div class="stats-card">
        <h2>Recommendations</h2>
        <ul class="circle-list">
            <li><strong>Improve Data Quality</strong>: Launch an educational campaign highlighting the benefits of consistent tracking across all metrics. Focus on increasing adoption of sleep and heart rate monitoring, where significant data gaps exist.</li>
            <li><strong>Target Low-Activity Users</strong>: Develop a tailored intervention program for users averaging under 5,000 daily steps. Implement gradual challenges and personalized encouragement to boost engagement and activity levels.</li>
            <li><strong>Promote Activity Balance</strong>: Create features that encourage a mix of intensity levels in daily activities. Highlight the potential benefits of balanced activity profiles, drawing on insights from users reporting better sleep quality.</li>
            <li><strong>Enhance Sleep Tracking</strong>: Address the high number of users with missing or low sleep data by improving sleep tracking features. Offer educational content on the importance of sleep and provide actionable tips for better sleep hygiene.</li>
            <li><strong>Increase Heart Rate Monitoring Engagement</strong>: Design targeted campaigns to boost heart rate data collection among the 20 users lacking this information. Emphasize the health insights gained from consistent heart rate monitoring.</li>
            <li><strong>Expand Comprehensive Health Tracking</strong>: Encourage holistic health monitoring by promoting weight tracking features. Develop integrated dashboards that showcase the interconnections between various health metrics.</li>
            <li><strong>Refine Goal-Setting Features</strong>: Leverage the observed activity polarization to create more nuanced, personalized goal-setting tools. Ensure goals are achievable yet challenging, adapting to individual user progress over time.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
